[[Wired_News|Wired News]]一连数年授予本作“最佳[[雾件|太监游戏]]奖”。本作在2000年名列第二，在2001和2002年蝉联第一。<ref name="whenever">Kahney, Leander. [http://www.wired.com/science/discoveries/news/2000/12/40484?currentPage=all "Vaporware 2000: Missing Inaction"] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20121208233201/www.wired.com/science/discoveries/news/2000/12/40484?currentPage=all |date=2012-12-08 }}. December 27, 2000. Wired News.</ref><ref>Manjoo, Farhad. [http://www.wired.com/news/technology/0,49326-1.html?tw=wn_story_page_next1 "Vaporware 2001: Empty Promises"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wired.com/news/technology/0,49326-1.html?tw=wn_story_page_next1 |date=20060721171842 }}. January 7, 2002. Wired News.</ref><ref name="ifever">Vaporware Team. [http://www.wired.com/culture/lifestyle/news/2003/01/57023?currentPage=all "Vaporware 2002: Tech Up in Smoke?"] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20121209035839/www.wired.com/culture/lifestyle/news/2003/01/57023?currentPage=all |date=2012-12-09 }}. ''Wired News''. January 3, 2003.</ref>该网站还专为本作设置了“太监游戏终身成就奖”，并于2003年颁发给本作。乔治·布罗撒接受了奖项并简单回应道“我们知道已跳票很久”。<ref>Vaporware Team Null. [http://www.wired.com/science/discoveries/news/2004/01/61935 "Vaporware: Nuke 'Em if Ya Got 'Em"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wired.com/science/discoveries/news/2004/01/61935 |date=20140206205725 }}. Wired News. January 20, 2004.</ref>2004年本作却未能出现在太监游戏前十强，Wired News编辑解释说他们颁发终身成就奖就是为了避免本作长期占着榜单。<ref name="neverever">Vaporware Team. [http://www.wired.com/culture/lifestyle/news/2005/01/66195 "Vaporware Phantom Haunts Us All"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wired.com/culture/lifestyle/news/2005/01/66195 |date=20131207083612 }}. January 7, 2005. Wired News.</ref>然而，鉴于读者的要求，Wired News改变了主意，让本作在2005，2006，2007年连续夺得太监游戏的頭銜。<ref>Kahney, Leander. [http://www.wired.com/science/discoveries/news/2006/02/70143 "Vaporware: Better Late Than Never"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wired.com/science/discoveries/news/2006/02/70143 |date=20140321142151 }}. Wired News. February 6, 2006.</ref><ref>Calore, Michael. [http://www.wired.com/software/softwarereviews/news/2006/12/72350 "Vaporware '06: Return of the King"] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120604142747/www.wired.com/software/softwarereviews/news/2006/12/72350 |date=2012-06-04 }}. Wired News. December 27, 2006.</ref><ref>Calore, Michael. [http://www.wired.com/gadgets/gadgetreviews/multimedia/2007/12/YE_Vaporware?slide=10&slideView=10 "Vaporware '07: Long Live the King"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wired.com/gadgets/gadgetreviews/multimedia/2007/12/YE_Vaporware?slide=10&slideView=10 |date=20121107131543 }}. Wired News. December 20, 2007.</ref>2008年，Wired网终于决定将本作永远撤下榜单，理由是“再好笑的笑话也有听腻的一天”。但考虑到本作游戏视频出现于Jace Hall Show，该站再次给予本作第一名的荣誉。<ref>Wired Staff. [http://www.wired.com/culture/culturereviews/news/2008/12/YE8_vaporware?currentPage=3 "Vaporware 2008: Crushing Disappointments, False Promises and Plain Old BS"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.wired.com/culture/culturereviews/news/2008/12/YE8_vaporware?currentPage=3 |date=20140210104645 }}. Wired News. December 29, 2008.</ref>

《永远的毁灭公爵》由于不断跳票而遭游戏媒体和玩家取笑，本作的标题，尤其是“永远的（Forever）”一词被替换为多种形式，例如“永不登场（Never）的毁灭公爵”，“让人好等（TakingForever）的毁灭公爵”，“爱来不来（Whenever）的毁灭公爵”，“干脆拉倒（Fornever）的毁灭公爵”，“千万别来（Neverever）的毁灭公爵”等。也有{{Who|玩家|time=2017-10-16}}主张本作的首字母缩写DNF也有“DID NOT FINISH（未完成赛道）”的意思。该短语在赛车运动中被广泛运用，形容因故（如机械故障或事故）未能跑完全程的选手。

2003年6月号[[GameSpy|GameSpy]]刊登了“游戏历史上最蠢的25个瞬间”，《永远的毁灭公爵》排名18。<ref>[http://archive.gamespy.com/articles/june03/dumbestmoments/index7.shtml "Never Bet on the Duke"] {{Wayback|url=http://archive.gamespy.com/articles/june03/dumbestmoments/index7.shtml |date=20120114164739 }}. Top 25 Dumbest Moments in Gaming History. GameSpy. June 10, 2003.</ref>

[[The_Jace_Hall_Show|The Jace Hall Show]]的主持人[[Jason_Hall_(producer)|Jason Hall]]在他2008年6月的第一期节目中玩过本作后形容本作很“完美”，评价道“我目击到了，确实能玩，不是谣传，都高兴去罢”。在采访中Hall开玩笑地询问布罗撒和米勒：“我满怀敬爱之情地请问一句，到底是怎么搞的拖这么久？”布罗撒也以玩笑话回应：“当然是有一点娼妓和[[可卡因|可卡因]]的因素，不过这些问题都解决了。现在最大的麻烦是《[[魔兽世界|魔兽世界]]》。”<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jacehallshow.com|title=The Jace Hall Show|accessdate=2008-06-04|archive-date=2016-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160127204421/http://jacehallshow.com/|dead-url=no}}</ref>在此后接受[[1UP.com|1UP.com]]采访时Hall形容本游戏“非常优秀”，“也许是唯一一部值得等待12年甚至更久去玩的游戏”。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.1up.com/do/newsStory?cId=3168117|title=Jason Hall Discusses His New Online Show|accessdate=May 7, 2009}}</ref>

